        <h1 class="mt-5">Typography</h1>
        <p class="display7 secondary mt-3">The CardX typography system uses a range of display classes to control the size of any font. While default sizes are applied to hierachical elements like h1, h2, h3, for the sake of consistency it is preferred to style all text with a display size class (eg. <code>.display7</code>) and an optional modifier (eg. <code>.secondary</code>).</p>
        <h2 class="mt-5">HTML Headings</h2>
        <p class="display7 secondary mt-3">HTML Headings have default styles that correlate directly to the display sizes. H1 elements are equivalent to Display 3 by default. Adding any display class to an HTML element will override the display </p>
        <table class="table mt-3">
            <thead>
                <tr class="display7">
                    <th>Code</th>
                    <th>Example</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-3"><code class="">&lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><span class="h1" >h1. Heading • 0.9 Opacity</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-3"><code >&lt;h2&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><span class="h2" >h2. Heading • 0.9 Opacity</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-3"><code >&lt;h3&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><span class="h3" >h3. Heading • 0.9 Opacity</span></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="mt-5">Display Headings</h2>
        <p class="display7 secondary mt-3">Using a display modifier is the preferable way to change the size of any text element.</p>
        <table class="table mt-4">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Code</th>
                    <th>Example</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">class="display1"</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="display1 my-0" >Display 1</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">class="display2"</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="display2 my-0" >Display 2</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">class="display3"</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="display3 my-0" >Display 3</p></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="mt-5 ">Style Modifiers</h2>
        <p class="display7 secondary mt-3">The style modifiers can be applied to any text element, like an HTML Heading <code class="">&lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</code>, <code class="">&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</code> or <code class="">&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code>.</p>
        <table class="table mt-4">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Code</th>
                    <th>Example</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="my-0">Paragraph Text</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="my-0"><strong>Strong Paragraph Text</strong></p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">&lt;p class='secondary'&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="secondary my-0">Secondary Paragraph Text</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">&lt;p class='disabled'&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="disabled my-0">Disabled Paragraph Text</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <p class="mx-0 my-0"><code class="">&lt;p class='accent'&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code></p>
                    </td>
                    <td><p class="accent my-0">Accented Paragraph Text</p></td>
                </tr>

            </tbody>
        </table>

